        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 10 at 8:50PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 850 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hardin, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail, along with brief
heavy rain and frequent lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hardin, Crow Agency and Crow Indian Reservation.

This storm will impact travel on Interstate 90 near Hardin.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
